[src:mlir-compiler/compiler-optimization] Reorder operations to allow multiple computations to happen in parallel, either at the instruction, memory, or thread level.
[src:mlir-compiler/compiler-optimization] The more precise the information the compiler has, the better it can employ any or all of these optimization techniques.
