[src:mlir-compiler/compiler-optimization] Another technique that attempts to reduce loop overhead.
[src:mlir-compiler/compiler-optimization] When two adjacent loops would iterate the same number of times regardless of whether that number is known at compile time, their bodies can be combined as long as they do not refer to each other's data.
